The paper deals with a dynamic variant of the k-center clustering problem, which involves maintaining a clustering with small approximation ratio while supporting an intermixed update sequence of insertions and deletions of points with small update time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The problem also involves working with metric spaces, which suggests that Computational Geometry (cs.CG) is another likely category. Additionally, the paper presents algorithms with approximation guarantees, which suggests that Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) are also possible categories.
